The United States expresses deep concern about the situation in Bahrain and calls for all parties to reject violence. They condemn violence against the police and government institutions, as well as the excessive use of force and tear gas against protestors, which has caused civilian casualties. The US urges the government and citizens of Bahrain to work together to address underlying issues and promote reconciliation. They also express concern for the jailed activist Abdulhadi Al-Khawaja and call on the Bahraini government to urgently resolve his case. The US encourages the government to implement the recommendations of the Bahrain Independent Commission of Inquiry and engage in a genuine dialogue for meaningful reforms that address the aspirations of all Bahrainis.